  "prompt": "How do I apply for PPF?",
  "response": "To apply for a Public Provident Fund (PPF) account in India, follow these steps:\n\n1. Documents Required:\n- Proof of identity (PAN card, Aadhaar card)\n- Proof of address\n- Passport-sized photographs\n- Filled PPF application form\n\n2. Eligibility:\n- Indian citizens can open a PPF account\n- Minors can open an account through their guardian\n- Non-Resident Indians (NRIs) cannot open new PPF accounts\n\n3. Where to Apply:\n- Designated bank branches (SBI, nationalized banks)\n- Post offices\n- Some private banks\n\n4. Application Process:\n- Obtain PPF application form\n- Fill out the form completely\n- Attach required documents\n- Submit the form with initial deposit\n- Minimum initial deposit is \u20b9500\n- Maximum annual deposit is \u20b91.5 lakh\n\n5. Account Details:\n- Account matures after 15 years\n- Partial withdrawals allowed after 6 years\n- Offers tax benefits under Section 80C\n- Currently offers around 7.1% interest rate (subject to change)\n\n6. Additional Tips:\n- Maintain minimum annual deposit of \u20b9500\n- Can make deposits online or at branch",
